By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja
(Sundiata Post) – President Muhammadu Buhari on Friday appointed Hassan Bashir
as the Acting Chairman of the National Population Commission (NPC). Hassan
Bashir takes over from the Executive Chairman, Eze Duruiheoma whose tenure
would end on January 23, 2019. Bashir
is to take charge of the commission activities till the appointment of a
substantive executive chairman.  

Source: Leadership